            . I am a <rs id="t18210912-69-viclabel378" type="occupation">currier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210912-69-victim767 t18210912-69-viclabel378"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18210912-69-crimeloc379">Whitecross-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18210912-69-crimeloc379" type="placeName" value="Whitecross-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18210912-69-crimeloc379" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210912-69-off376 t18210912-69-crimeloc379"></join>. On the 25th of July, about half-past ten o'clock, at night, the coat was in my chaise by my side; I was in my own yard, coming home. As I drove up the yard and stopped, two men ran up the yard after the chaise, and I felt the coat go from my side, looked round and saw two men running away with it; I jumped out and secured the prisoner, who was one of them; his companion ran off with the coat, it was worth 2 l., the yard is no thoroughfare.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210912-69-person769">
